<username>Matthew Sprague< /username>< user_id>
107579218965393068352<//user_id>
< Text>
OK so went to Lynwood and met with Mike Stambouli of Via Trading on Monday. Our business has shifted it's model currently and we are attempting to move into liquidation based items, etc. etc.
Had emailed Mike back and forth so he could get a feel about what we were interested in getting for our store. So we made the trip to Lynwood to meet with Mike on Monday and I gotta say we were met at the door by Mike and he proceeded to spend a huge amount of time with us answering questions showing us loads from pallets to truckloads from Walmart to Shopko and everything in between. He was knowledgeable, patient, and best of all was not high pressure at all.
Being new to sourcing merchandise from liquidation type places was whole new territory to us. Mike did a great job introducing us to it all and letting us take it all in. All we can say is thanks again for truly taking the time to walk us through the process of it all.

All that said A+++ review for Mike personally. Now onto the product we purchased. We knew going down we wanted tools and that was a priority for us. We had wanted to potentially buy a truckload of general merchandise to have shipped back. We saw many Walmart loads and all seemed to be good enough to turn profit at the price they were selling for. The best truckloads we saw were the shopko loads they are huge and have a huge variety and outside impressions were extremely good and after getting all googly eyed about them and nearly pulling the trigger on one we decided to wait purely because of space restraints and help to process that size of a load. Logistics on our end stopped us from making the purchase not any doubt as to the return we could make on the load.
They had 5 pallet lots of Harbor freight tools as well as a truckload of harbor frieght tools we ended up buying 2 of the 5 pallet lots of tools basically to get an idea of how this would all work. We were nervous but they were decent looking pallets very little obviously broken items actually only 1 battery charger was the only item there was no doubt was beyond repair.
Today we started processing the load of 10 pallets of tools. We were expecting a solid 20% loss and am extremely happy to report we at about 80% to 90% processed we haven't even filled a large tote with the items that haven't worked or were broken and in need of repair. On top of that the items that have been bad were items that would have retailed between 20 and 50 bucks and honestly I feel like most can be repaired with minor work ( Switches, brushes etc.) We got a ton of compressors the small pancake type like 20 of them all of them except 1 worked with the issue that most likely got them returned being gauges that didn't work well at the price point we have them at nobody cares ( we sold 6 of them today ) have had 4 items that were clearly well used and returned but still functioned and with cleaning will be easy sells.
A few items maybe 5% will take a long time to sell like shallow well pumps things like that but it's of no concern because given what we saw today and what we've seen in the past with tools we will have a vast majority sold within a week. Very exciting!
It was a great mix of items with very few hand tools. Mostly drills Sawzall compressors 8 welders all working only 1 with a missing tip, 3 winches, bandsaws, mitre saws ( sold 2 today already and every one we got worked fine) small hand held power tools to large shop tools.
So long story short and I know that every load is different and another may be the complete opposite but in this load and in our case we can't say enough good things. From Mike as our sales person to the goods we bought. We will in the end double our money and then some. Seriously was a top notch experience top to bottom.
I read some bad reviews about Via Trading and we were nervous but we all know everyone is quick to give bad reviews but the good ones aren't so frequent I told Mike I would give an honest review of the experience and the merchandise and this was it.</Text>

<text>I had to go to here on Mother's day after my domestic house cat attacked me pretty bad. I was worried at first because of the "covid19 thing" but Im glad I went, to my surprise there was no other patients waiting, I was actually the only one.
The place was very clean, all staff had on masks and it felt safe. < review>
worst experience ever.  I scheduled an appointment with them, gave my insurance information over the phone. Reached before time, gave my insurance card and filled in the registration form. I had pre-authorization from my Insurance company to visit any Urgent Care and my insurance company did confirm this to the provider over the phone & fax that they will cover all the claims as I needed urgent medical attention for toe which got cut by a blade. Some of the food was good, and I'm told it's not normally like this, but on a really quiet Thursday night our server was pretty inattentive, we had to get up to ask for things like silverware and napkins, then the ultimate ruiner for me was biting into a piece of tempura broccoli and finding it was rotten inside.  Since we had ordered two dishes that had it, my girlfriend gave me hers to try, which also turned out to be only slightly less rotten.

It's hard to imagine that started out rotten and was battered anyway, which suggests they're storing food far too long after prep, which is also scary.  The remainder of my night was spent nauseated by the taste of this rancid broccoli over and over again, which I couldn't seem to mask.

I don't think I'm willing to give them another shot for a while.<//text>

< Review>
I time to time stop at buffalo wild wings restaurants for some wings and drink, recently they heavily advertised their all American hamburger.

Last night i stopped at their culver and 5 free way restaurant and ordered the horrible oily greasy all American hamburger.

This is just another food scam by buffalo wild wings restaurants, the $20 burger was nearly 70% beef and 30% fats, very greasy and oily, thin beef patty's, oily grilled onions setting on chopped lettuce, the Cesar salad i ordered was 50% croutons and very bad quality lettuce, very terrible salad.

The burger was not only tasteless but very fatty and oily, their fountain Pepsi drink @ $3.79 plus tax is more expensive than Morton steak house soft drinks, a total ripoff.

Looking at my experience, it was terrible from lousy host at the door to the service provided and horrible food, i don't recommend this Restaurant neither i do recommend the horrible all American hamburger, putting the $20 for the lousy burger and $5 tip the Restaurant is total ripoff.<//Review>

<response>None</response><rating>2</rating><review>In the ever present rivalry between BWW and Wingstop, the wing-off is won and lost in the execution. There are a few ways that the chicken here could be improved.

The chicken could definitely be juicier. The meat was dry and stringy. Then they can afford to put a bit more sauce on the wings. I don't know how much money they are saving from the reduced quantity of sauce, but they are losing revenue on people choosing their rivals.

<text>In the ever present rivalry between BWW and Wingstop, the wing-off is won and lost in the execution. There are a few ways that the chicken here could be improved.

The chicken could definitely be juicier. The meat was dry and stringy. Then they can afford to put a bit more sauce on the wings. I don't know how much money they are saving from the reduced quantity of sauce, but they are losing revenue on people choosing their rivals.

The most mind numbing part is the service. No one is available to ask for the check, or refills, or asking questions. You have sit and wait... and wait... and wait. Not fun. I don't know why I came here...<//text></record></dataset><record>

<username>Karl Werner<//username>< pics>
None< /pics>
< review>
It is quite an experience. The food is good, actually is is very tasty. Polite people. We ordered online and that is an easy thing. We decided to have their speciel Thursday offer which has a very good price. The difficulty is when your pick up the product you have to have a profile in their system to get this speciel price. Nowhere they mentioned that during the order process. When I picked up they asked for my profile. We do not have one so they  gave me a flimsy tablet to set up a profile. After I realized that people were waiting behind me I decided to pay the normal price and refused to set up a profile.

Where I went to the university I learned these kind of practice is called misleading customers and is illegal. But ,hey, that was centuries ago.

Nevertheless the food is great and the service is great.</review>
